Problem: Implement an algorithm for determining if an Nth is a divisor of an n Number (i.e. 2 is a divisor of 6). If so, determine if it’s an even number or odd number as well. 

SOLUTION 

1. Ask user for a n number  

2. Ask user for a Nth number 

3. if n % N1 == 0  

4. Then display “N1 is a divisor of n” 

5. else display “N1 is not a divisor of n” 

6. if N1 % 2 == 0 

7. Then display “N1 is an even number” 

8. else display “N1 is an odd number” 

Problem: Implement an algorithm for making a simple calculator with all the operators (+,-,*,/,%) 

SOLUTION 

1. Ask user for a N1 number  

2. Ask user for a N2 number 

3. Ask user for a A variable 

4. Set Result to garbage value 

5. if A = +  

6. Then Result = N1 + N2  

7. Display “The result is” , Result 

8. else if A = - 

9. Then Result = N1 - N2  

10. Display “The result is” , Result 

11. else if A = * 

12. Then Result = N1 * N2  

13. Display “The result is” , Result 

14. else if A = / 

15. Then Result = N1 / N2  

16. Display “The result is” , Result 

17. else display “invalid operator” 
